      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Will Metastable give me a caffeine-like buzz?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">No. Metastable is caffeine-free and stimulant-free. The energy comes from restored cellular machinery — B-complex cofactors, better absorption through a healthier gut, and a calmer stress response. It's steady, not spiky.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is ashwagandha safe to take every day?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">KSM-66 ashwagandha has the largest body of safety data of any extract — with studies running 12 weeks or more of daily use. We recommend a natural break (5 days on, 2 off, or an 8-week cycle) the same way most clinicians do with any adaptogen.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I take Metastable with Collabloom or Collatrim?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Collabloom focuses on beauty, Collatrim on body composition, Metastable on the internal terrain — gut, stress, energy. Space collagen-containing products an hour apart so you're not stacking the same 5g dose twice in a window.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is Metastable safe during pregnancy or breastfeeding?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">We don't recommend Metastable during pregnancy or breastfeeding — ashwagandha and rhodiola haven't been adequately studied in those windows. Speak with your obstetrician before adding any adaptogen supplement.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Does Metastable contain any allergens?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Contains marine collagen (fish). Free from dairy, gluten, soy and nuts. Not vegan. Inulin is derived from chicory root — mild bloating can occur in the first week as the microbiome adapts. This typically resolves by week two.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What's your return policy?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Adaptogens take time. We ask you to give Metastable at least 30 days of consistent use before judging the outcome — KSM-66 and Rhodiola both have published timelines around the 28–42 day mark.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

